<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="212" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,474,1986]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,474,499]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Scutum with median longitudinal band; tergites and sternites brownish (
<figureCitation box="[1107,1192,474,499]" captionStart="FIGURES 51 – 55" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1938,1961]" captionTargetBox="[211,1376,193,1912]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[210,1377,193,1917]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 51 – 55. Hemerodromia ubajaraensis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 51, habitus, lateral view; 52, terminalia, lateral view; 53, ejaculatory apodeme, subepandrial sclerite and surstylus, dorsal view; 54, gonocoxal apodeme, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view; 55, epandrium and hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233680/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="212">
Fig. 
<number box="[1161,1192,474,499]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212" value="51.0">51</number>
</figureCitation>
); epandrium fused to hypandrium; phallus with pointed dorsal projection apically and membranous area covered with spicules and hooklike bifid apical process (
<figureCitation box="[433,517,546,571]" captionStart="FIGURES 51 – 55" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1938,1961]" captionTargetBox="[211,1376,193,1912]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[210,1377,193,1917]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 51 – 55. Hemerodromia ubajaraensis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 51, habitus, lateral view; 52, terminalia, lateral view; 53, ejaculatory apodeme, subepandrial sclerite and surstylus, dorsal view; 54, gonocoxal apodeme, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view; 55, epandrium and hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233680/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="212">
Fig. 
<number box="[485,517,546,571]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212" value="54.0">54</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="212" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,474,1986]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,582,607]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212">Description</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[356,417,582,607]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212">Male</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[437,526,582,607]" captionStart="FIGURES 51 – 55" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1938,1961]" captionTargetBox="[211,1376,193,1912]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[210,1377,193,1917]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 51 – 55. Hemerodromia ubajaraensis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 51, habitus, lateral view; 52, terminalia, lateral view; 53, ejaculatory apodeme, subepandrial sclerite and surstylus, dorsal view; 54, gonocoxal apodeme, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view; 55, epandrium and hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233680/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="212">
Fig. 
<number box="[495,526,582,607]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212" value="51.0">51</number>
</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[551,615,582,607]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212">Head</emphasis>
. Dark brown to black, antenna and mouthparts yellow with all setae whitish. Ocellar triangle with 
<number box="[484,498,619,643]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212" value="1.0">1</number>
pair of proclinate setae; anterior ocellus larger. Eyes iridescent black, very narrowly separated on face bearing fine reclinate setulae. Frons with 
<number box="[878,919,655,679]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2</number>
frontal setulae; 
<number box="[1121,1163,655,679]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3</number>
pairs of vertical setae contiguous with uniseriate row of postocular setae. Occiput bearing scattered fine hairs. Clypeus with rather dense, short downwardly directed pile. Proboscis slightly curved with yellow setae. Antenna with scape and pedicel bearing distinct, short dorsal setulae; postpedicel about 
<number box="[775,808,763,787]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212" value="1.3">1.3</number>
X as long as wide, stylus ~ 
<number box="[1120,1155,763,787]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212" value="0.9">0.9</number>
X as long as postpedicel. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,240,798,823]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212">Thorax</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[256,340,798,823]" captionStart="FIGURES 51 – 55" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1938,1961]" captionTargetBox="[211,1376,193,1912]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[210,1377,193,1917]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 51 – 55. Hemerodromia ubajaraensis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 51, habitus, lateral view; 52, terminalia, lateral view; 53, ejaculatory apodeme, subepandrial sclerite and surstylus, dorsal view; 54, gonocoxal apodeme, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view; 55, epandrium and hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233680/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="212">
Fig. 
<number box="[309,340,798,823]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212" value="51.0">51</number>
</figureCitation>
). Elongate, slightly arched ventrally; thoracic dorsum yellowish, except brownish on prothoracic collar, narrowly behind postpronotal lobe, above wing base, median longitudinal band on scutum, suture between katepisternum and meron, katepisternum ventrally behind C 
<number box="[857,868,871,895]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212" value="1.0">1</number>
, scutellum and mediotergite; antepronotum with anterior margin almost straight and scutum with yellow setae, very small and fine except 
<number box="[1156,1170,907,931]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212" value="1.0">1</number>
notopleural. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1319,1375,906,931]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212">Legs</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 51 – 55" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1938,1961]" captionTargetBox="[211,1376,193,1912]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[210,1377,193,1917]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 51 – 55. Hemerodromia ubajaraensis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 51, habitus, lateral view; 52, terminalia, lateral view; 53, ejaculatory apodeme, subepandrial sclerite and surstylus, dorsal view; 54, gonocoxal apodeme, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view; 55, epandrium and hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233680/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="212">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,182,942,967]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212" value="51.0">51</number>
</figureCitation>
). Whitish yellow. C 
<number box="[419,429,943,967]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212" value="1.0">1</number>
~ 
<number box="[465,499,943,967]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212" value="1.2">1.2</number>
X longer than distance between C 
<number box="[900,910,943,967]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212" value="1.0">1</number>
and C2, 
<date box="[1022,1056,942,967]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212">5X</date>
as long as wide with some pale dorsoapical setae. F 
<number box="[380,390,979,1003]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212" value="1.0">1</number>
about 
<number box="[470,504,979,1003]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212" value="1.2">1.2</number>
X as long as C 
<number box="[679,690,979,1003]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212" value="1.0">1</number>
, 
<number box="[704,738,978,1003]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212" value="3.5">3.5</number>
–4.0X as long as wide. Femoral formula 
<number box="[1209,1250,978,1003]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212" value="7.5" valueMax="9.0" valueMin="6.0">
6– 
<date box="[1237,1250,978,1003]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212" value="1922-09-20" valueMax="1922-09-21" valueMin="1922-09-20">9</date>
</number>
/ 
<number box="[1259,1329,978,1003]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212" value="20.5" valueMax="21.0" valueMin="20.0">20–21</number>
/ 
<number box="[1339,1410,978,1003]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212" value="22.5" valueMax="23.0" valueMin="22.0">22–23</number>
/ 
<number box="[1419,1432,978,1003]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212" value="6.0">6</number>
; denticles confined to distal 
<number box="[458,495,1015,1039]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212" value="0.7">0.7</number>
, becoming closer together distally, black, 
<number box="[966,980,1015,1039]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212" value="2.0">2</number>
rows linear, without distal discontinuity, diverging abruptly at extreme apex. T 
<number box="[577,587,1051,1075]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212" value="1.0">1</number>
~ 
<number box="[617,652,1051,1075]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212" value="0.7">0.7</number>
X as long as F 
<number box="[818,829,1051,1075]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212" value="1.0">1</number>
, evenly curved, ventral face shallowly concave; about 
<number box="[151,221,1087,1111]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212" value="18.0" valueMax="19.0" valueMin="17.0">17–19</number>
sharply pointed spinose setae ventrally; dorsal ciliation of decumbent short, pale setulae, denser distally; without apicoventral extension on T 
<number box="[560,571,1123,1147]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212" value="1.0">1</number>
, with strong apical spine. Mid- and hind legs slender with fine setae; T 
<number box="[1367,1379,1123,1147]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212" value="3.0">3</number>
with ‘comb’ of short setae posteroapically. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[578,643,1158,1183]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212">Wing</emphasis>
. Membrane slightly yellow, veins brownish; R 
<number box="[1167,1175,1173,1187]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number box="[1184,1191,1173,1187]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212" value="3.0">3</number>
long and straight, not strongly curved towards C apically, joining C ~ 
<number box="[700,735,1198,1222]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212" value="0.7">0.7</number>
distance between end of R 
<number box="[1045,1053,1212,1226]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212" value="1.0">1</number>
and R 
<number box="[1128,1136,1212,1226]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212" value="4.0">4</number>
+ 
<number box="[1145,1152,1212,1226]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212" value="5.0">5</number>
; R 
<number box="[1187,1195,1212,1226]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212" value="4.0">4</number>
+ 
<number box="[1205,1212,1212,1226]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212" value="5.0">5</number>
fork angle acute (~ 
<number box="[151,183,1236,1261]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212" value="60.0">60</number>
°), distal to position of M 
<number box="[461,466,1251,1265]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212" value="1.0">1</number>
+ 
<number box="[476,485,1251,1265]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212" value="2.0">2</number>
fork by about same length as R 
<number box="[839,847,1251,1265]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212" value="4.0">4</number>
; R 
<number box="[880,888,1251,1265]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212" value="5.0">5</number>
and M 
<number box="[966,974,1251,1265]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212" value="1.0">1</number>
convergent distally; R 
<number box="[1228,1236,1251,1265]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212" value="5.0">5</number>
~ 2.0X as long as R 
<number box="[169,177,1290,1304]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212" value="4.0">4</number>
; cell bm+dm short, ending just before R 
<number box="[639,647,1290,1304]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212" value="1.0">1</number>
, ~2.0X as long as cell br. Halter whitish yellow. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1205,1321,1275,1300]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212">Abdomen</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1338,1422,1275,1300]" captionStart="FIGURES 51 – 55" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1938,1961]" captionTargetBox="[211,1376,193,1912]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[210,1377,193,1917]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 51 – 55. Hemerodromia ubajaraensis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 51, habitus, lateral view; 52, terminalia, lateral view; 53, ejaculatory apodeme, subepandrial sclerite and surstylus, dorsal view; 54, gonocoxal apodeme, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view; 55, epandrium and hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233680/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="212">
Fig. 
<number box="[1391,1422,1275,1300]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212" value="51.0">51</number>
</figureCitation>
). Tergites and sternites brownish; tergite 
<number box="[617,631,1314,1338]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212" value="8.0">8</number>
shorter than sternite 
<number box="[887,903,1314,1338]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212" value="8.0">8</number>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[920,1051,1313,1338]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212">Terminalia</emphasis>
. Brown. Cercus narrow, pointed apically (
<figureCitation box="[262,353,1349,1374]" captionStart="FIGURES 51 – 55" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1938,1961]" captionTargetBox="[211,1376,193,1912]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[210,1377,193,1917]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 51 – 55. Hemerodromia ubajaraensis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 51, habitus, lateral view; 52, terminalia, lateral view; 53, ejaculatory apodeme, subepandrial sclerite and surstylus, dorsal view; 54, gonocoxal apodeme, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view; 55, epandrium and hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233680/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="212">
Fig. 
<number box="[322,353,1349,1374]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212" value="52.0">52</number>
</figureCitation>
), left and right cerci closely approximated anterodorsally, distinctly setose on outer face. Epandrium widened basally, slightly pointed apically (
<figureCitation box="[776,862,1385,1410]" captionStart="FIGURES 51 – 55" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1938,1961]" captionTargetBox="[211,1376,193,1912]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[210,1377,193,1917]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 51 – 55. Hemerodromia ubajaraensis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 51, habitus, lateral view; 52, terminalia, lateral view; 53, ejaculatory apodeme, subepandrial sclerite and surstylus, dorsal view; 54, gonocoxal apodeme, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view; 55, epandrium and hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233680/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="212">
Fig. 
<number box="[831,862,1385,1410]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212" value="52.0">52</number>
</figureCitation>
), scattered setae on outer; fused with hypandrium (
<figureCitation box="[159,249,1421,1446]" captionStart="FIGURES 51 – 55" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1938,1961]" captionTargetBox="[211,1376,193,1912]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[210,1377,193,1917]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 51 – 55. Hemerodromia ubajaraensis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 51, habitus, lateral view; 52, terminalia, lateral view; 53, ejaculatory apodeme, subepandrial sclerite and surstylus, dorsal view; 54, gonocoxal apodeme, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view; 55, epandrium and hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233680/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="212">
Fig. 
<number box="[217,249,1421,1446]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212" value="55.0">55</number>
</figureCitation>
). Surstylus subrounded, with setae at apex (
<figureCitation box="[778,920,1421,1446]" captionStart="FIGURES 51 – 55" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1938,1961]" captionTargetBox="[211,1376,193,1912]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[210,1377,193,1917]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 51 – 55. Hemerodromia ubajaraensis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 51, habitus, lateral view; 52, terminalia, lateral view; 53, ejaculatory apodeme, subepandrial sclerite and surstylus, dorsal view; 54, gonocoxal apodeme, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view; 55, epandrium and hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233680/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="212">Figs 52, 54</figureCitation>
). Hypandrium subrectangular (
<figureCitation box="[1285,1374,1421,1446]" captionStart="FIGURES 51 – 55" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1938,1961]" captionTargetBox="[211,1376,193,1912]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[210,1377,193,1917]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 51 – 55. Hemerodromia ubajaraensis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 51, habitus, lateral view; 52, terminalia, lateral view; 53, ejaculatory apodeme, subepandrial sclerite and surstylus, dorsal view; 54, gonocoxal apodeme, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view; 55, epandrium and hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233680/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="212">
Fig. 
<number box="[1343,1374,1421,1446]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212" value="55.0">55</number>
</figureCitation>
), not inflated, with distinct setae; gonocoxal apodeme projecting as narrow process just beyond anterior margin of hypandrium (
<figureCitation box="[304,440,1493,1518]" captionStart="FIGURES 51 – 55" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1938,1961]" captionTargetBox="[211,1376,193,1912]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[210,1377,193,1917]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 51 – 55. Hemerodromia ubajaraensis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 51, habitus, lateral view; 52, terminalia, lateral view; 53, ejaculatory apodeme, subepandrial sclerite and surstylus, dorsal view; 54, gonocoxal apodeme, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view; 55, epandrium and hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233680/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="212">Figs 52, 54</figureCitation>
). Subepandrial sclerite narrow, without posterior process (
<figureCitation box="[1113,1199,1493,1518]" captionStart="FIGURES 51 – 55" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1938,1961]" captionTargetBox="[211,1376,193,1912]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[210,1377,193,1917]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 51 – 55. Hemerodromia ubajaraensis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 51, habitus, lateral view; 52, terminalia, lateral view; 53, ejaculatory apodeme, subepandrial sclerite and surstylus, dorsal view; 54, gonocoxal apodeme, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view; 55, epandrium and hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233680/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="212">
Fig. 
<number box="[1168,1199,1493,1518]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212" value="53.0">53</number>
</figureCitation>
). Phallus sclerotized basally, extending just beyond hypandrium apex, with pointed dorsal projection apically; membranous area covered with spicules and hook-like bifid apical process (
<figureCitation box="[832,921,1565,1590]" captionStart="FIGURES 51 – 55" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1938,1961]" captionTargetBox="[211,1376,193,1912]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[210,1377,193,1917]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 51 – 55. Hemerodromia ubajaraensis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 51, habitus, lateral view; 52, terminalia, lateral view; 53, ejaculatory apodeme, subepandrial sclerite and surstylus, dorsal view; 54, gonocoxal apodeme, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view; 55, epandrium and hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233680/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="212">
Fig. 
<number box="[889,921,1565,1590]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212" value="54.0">54</number>
</figureCitation>
). Ejaculatory apodeme unilamellar flattened anteroposteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[358,442,1601,1626]" captionStart="FIGURES 51 – 55" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1938,1961]" captionTargetBox="[211,1376,193,1912]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[210,1377,193,1917]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 51 – 55. Hemerodromia ubajaraensis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 51, habitus, lateral view; 52, terminalia, lateral view; 53, ejaculatory apodeme, subepandrial sclerite and surstylus, dorsal view; 54, gonocoxal apodeme, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view; 55, epandrium and hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233680/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="212">
Fig. 
<number box="[410,442,1601,1626]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212" value="53.0">53</number>
</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[461,658,1601,1626]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212">Specimen length</emphasis>
: 
<quantity box="[672,761,1602,1626]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" pageId="15" pageNumber="212" unit="mm" value="2.7">2.7 mm</quantity>
